e care the stanford faculty & staff help center is available to all employees medical contribution assistance program to make it easier for you to provide medical coverage for your family we created the medical contribution assistance program mcap if you qualify the program pays up to the full employee contribution of the lowest cost medical plan when you cover a spouse and or children read the mcap guidelines and download an application dental plans stanford offers two delta dental plan options that provide coverage for dental care through delta dental's network of dentists you may also see a dentist outside of delta's network delta dental ppo delta premier compare dental plans vision care stanford offers vision care that includes coverage for eyeglasses and contacts through vision service plan vsp staying healthy stanford offers programs and services to promote your ongoing health and well being flexible spending accounts our flexible spending accounts fsas help you plan for certain expenses while reducing your taxes check out our health and dependent day care fsas health savings account if you enroll in the blue shield high deductible ppo and are eligible for a personal health savings account hsa we offer easy enrollment and the opportunity to contribute via payroll enrolling in your plans you may enroll yourself and your eligible dependents within 31 days of becoming an eligible employee new coverage elections can be made during open enrollment each fall to be effective january 1 of the following year changes can only be made outside the enrollment period if you or a covered family member have a life event change quick links find out about eligibility selecting a medical plan hmo or ppo compare medical plans compare dental plans learn about coverage in retirement cobra hipaa resources plan summaries rate sheets forms mcap contacts medical plan providers delta dental vision service plan vsp flexible spending accounts stanford faculty & staff help center home bene